{
  "text": "Bi et al. [CITATION_1] proposed a multi-stage fully convolutional networks (FCNs) for skin lesions segmentation. The multi-stage involved localised coarse appearance learning in the early stage and detailed boundaries characteristics learning in the later stage. Further, they implemented a parallel integration approach to enable fusion of the result that they claimed that this has enhanced the detection. Their method outperformed others in PH2 dataset [CITATION_2] of 90.66% but achieved marginal improvement if compared to Team ExB in ISIB 2016 competition with 91.18%.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "206616262",
